column3: A genius inventor and billionaire industrialist who becomes the superhero Iron Man.
A frail young man enhanced to the peak of human perfection by an experimental serum to become the superhero Captain America.
A highly trained spy and former assassin known as Black Widow, affiliated with the superhero team, the Avengers.
A young man who gains spider-like abilities after being bitten by a radioactive spider, becoming the superhero Spider-Man.
Also known as Wolverine, a mutant with regenerative healing powers, retractable claws, and a fierce warrior.
A mercenary with accelerated healing powers and a twisted sense of humor, known as Deadpool.
A young wizard who discovers his magical heritage on his eleventh birthday, known for his battle against the dark wizard Voldemort.
A young FBI trainee who seeks the advice of the imprisoned Dr. Hannibal Lecter to catch another serial killer.
A gentle and kind-hearted heroine from the classic novel and film, 'Gone with the Wind', known for her love story with Rhett Butler.
A charming and cunning man from 'Gone with the Wind', famous for his tumultuous relationship with Scarlett O'Hara.
A new blade runner for the Los Angeles Police Department who uncovers a long-buried secret that has the potential to plunge society into chaos.
A talented memory designer who creates false memories for replicants in 'Blade Runner 2049'.
A hobbit of the Shire who undertakes a perilous journey to destroy the One Ring in the fires of Mount Doom.
Frodo's uncle who first finds the One Ring and goes on an adventure with a group of dwarves in 'The Hobbit'.
A man with a low IQ but good intentions, whose simple approach to life leads him through historical events across the United States.
A theoretical physicist known for developing the theory of relativity, one of the two pillars of modern physics.
The 16th president of the United States, who led the nation through its Civil War and abolished slavery.
The 46th president of the United States, previously serving as vice president under Barack Obama.
An Oscar-winning actress known for her versatility in film roles and her advocacy for women's rights and HIV/AIDS awareness.
A former professional basketball player widely regarded as one of the greatest in the history of the sport.
A former professional basketball player known for his immense size and personality, as well as his dominance on the court.
